SIMPLE: picked
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Picked
<hw>Pick"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pointed;
sharp.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Picked</xex> and polished.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let the stake be made <qex>picked</qex> at the top.</q>
<rj><qau>Mortimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a pike or spine on the
back; -- said of certain fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Carefully selected; chosen; <as>as, <ex>picked</ex>
men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Fine; spruce; smart; precise; dainty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Picked dogfish</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Dogfish</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Picked out</b></col>,
<cd>ornamented or relieved with lines, or the like, of a different,
usually a lighter, color; as, a carriage body dark green, <xex>picked
out</xex> with red.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pickedness</ent>⟦br⟧
